Decalre gloalvariable of types int, char, float,and double without initializing them. Print the values and observe the output. 
Do the same for local variables.
#include<stdio.h>
int num;
char ch;
float f;
double d;
int main()
{
    int num ;
    char ch;
    float f;
    double d;
    printf("%d %c %f %lf",num,ch,f,d);
    return 0;
}
